# Main Entities in the Diagram
(1) User
This is the main table for login information.

# Attributes:
user_id (PK)
email (unique)
password_hash
first_name
last_name
role (Doctor / Patient)
phone_number
# Relationship:
One User → One Doctor
One User → One Patient

(2)Doctor

Stores doctor-specific information.

# Attributes:
doctor_id (PK)
user_id (FK)
specialization_id (FK)
hospital_name
experience_years
active
updated_at
# Relationships:
Many Doctors → One Specialization
One Doctor → Many Availability Slots
One Doctor → Many Services
One Doctor → Many Appointments

(3)Specialization

Stores medical fields.

# Attributes:
specialization_id (PK)
doctor_id (FK)
specialization (e.g., Cardiology)
# One Specialization can be linked with multiple doctors.

(4)Service

Services provided by doctor.

Attributes:
service_id (PK)
doctor_id (FK)
name
# One Doctor → Many Services 

(5) Doctor_Availability

Stores available time slots of doctor.
# Attributes:
availability_id (PK)
doctor_id (FK)
date
day_of_week
start_time
end_time
max_appointments
session
active
updated_at
# One Doctor → Many Availability Slots
# One Slot → Many Appointments

(6)Patients

Stores patient details.
# Attributes:
patient_id (PK)
user_id (FK)
gender
medical_history
emergency_contact
# One Patient → Many Appointments

(7)Appointment

Main table that connects Patient and Doctor.
# Attributes:
appointment_id (PK)
patient_id (FK)
doctor_id (FK)
availability_id (FK)
token_number
appointment_start
status (Pending / Completed / Failed)
paid_at

# One Appointment → One Payment
# One Appointment → One Feedback

(8)Payment

Stores payment details.

# Attributes:
payment_id (PK)
appointment_id (FK)
amount
payment_method (Cash / Online / Card)
status
paid_at
# One Appointment → One Payment

(9)Feedback

Stores patient feedback after appointment.

# Attributes:
feedback_id (PK)
appointment_id (FK)
doctor_rating
hospital_rating
overall_rating
comments
# One Appointment → One Feedback




